## Utility Function
The `cn()` function in [src/lib/utils.tsx](mdc:src/lib/utils.tsx) combines `clsx` and `tailwind-merge`:

```typescript
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

// Conditional classes
<div className={cn(
  "base-classes",
  condition && "conditional-classes",
  className // allows external className override
)}>
```

### Component Variants
Use `class-variance-authority` for component variants:

```typescript
import { cva } from 'class-variance-authority';

const buttonVariants = cva(
  "base-classes",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        primary: "bg-violet-600 hover:bg-violet-700 text-white",
        secondary: "bg-zinc-800 hover:bg-zinc-700 text-white",
      },
      size: {
        sm: "px-3 py-1.5 text-sm",
        md: "px-4 py-2 text-base",
        lg: "px-6 py-3 text-lg",
      }
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "primary",
      size: "md",
    }
  }
);
```

## Responsive Design

### Mobile-First Approach
- Start with mobile styles
- Use Tailwind breakpoints: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Test on multiple screen sizes

### Mobile Detection
Use the mobile hook from [src/hooks/use-mobile.tsx](mdc:src/hooks/use-mobile.tsx):

```typescript
import { useIsMobile } from '@/hooks/use-mobile';

function Component() {
  const isMobile = useIsMobile();

  return (
    <div className={isMobile ? "mobile-classes" : "desktop-classes"}>
      {/* Content */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Accessibility Patterns

### Radix UI Integration
All components use Radix UI primitives for accessibility:
